be the bartender find me a drink alright i'm a year old black male who has just started drinking i have done some experimenting with stuff but i dont know what kind of drink i would order if i was in a bar or something i m looking for something that tastes good but not a sissy drink something sophisticated but not too strong i like grey goose but not straight long island ice teas are alright to me i dont like beer but i like smirnoffs and stuff like that grey goose and cranberry this is what people most often order grey goose with oz seagram's oz up sprite rick james oz hennesey oz bacardi oz up sprite liquid cocaine i only recommend this if you want to forget what happened that night alot of bartenders have different ways of making it this is how i make it and my customers swear they never have been drunker faster oz goldschlager oz jagermeister oz bacardi i drink cuba libre oz rum white like bacardi superior oz lime juice its better with juice and not just a lime oz coke it tastes good goes down easy and doesn't qualify as sissy just don't ever order a fuzzy navel or sex on the beach and any man who orders a martini is bound to get a few weird looks thats just the way it is Rum Cocktail Martini cocktail Little Britain Bloody Mary (cocktail) Long Island Iced Tea Alcoholic beverage Avenue Q Friends Trainspotting (novel) Moonshine Homer Simpson Moe Szyslak Ron and Fez RuneScape quests Birthday Sin City Daiquiri Phoebe Buffay's songs Pitaten The Shining (film) Cuba Libre Social rule Trailer Park Boys Bartender Grog One Tree Hill (TV series) The Smoking Room Cacha__a Drink The Ashlee Simpson Show Satchel Paige Knots Landing Wolfrider Garfield Mountain Dew Halitosis Bacardi Weebl and Bob The Drew Carey Show AFI 100 Years series A Clockwork Orange Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Cider The Emancipation of Mimi Cuisine of Denmark Drinking culture The Wack Pack Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Jon Secada Good Morning, Vietnam Conker's Bad Fur Day About a Boy Gin Brian G